snippet.textDisplay:
Actually, I don’t think he missed the "sweet quarantine" idea. I think he thought about it and decided it took too much away from the familiarity and comfort of the song that we all love to sing along with. I think he changed it enough to make us laugh a little but kept it mostly the same to also offer not just a little humor but understanding and support. The original lyrics offer compassion and love if you really listen. If he changed it to, "Sweet Quarantine" and changed the all of lyrics into something hysterically funny, that would lack a lot of empathy for those going through this virus - either themselves or their loved ones. Just my opinion. :)
Besides, there is really nothing sweet about being quarantined. Stay safe and well everyone. Much love!

snippet.textDisplay: Right at the end of January I started to get down because the conditions were worsening globally and I started to cry for the world. We just had the Holidays but I needed a sense of inspiration and a quick spiritual zap to focus priorities, beyond a new year's resolution, for what may come. So I recalled Henry Wrinkler's line to Kevin James, about choosing an entrance song for the fighter in Here Comes the Boom, when he said about the song, "It got me through a very difficult time". So thinking about a song for getting ready to go through a difficult time led me to Holly Holy, and hearing it a few times did the job. Sweet Caroline, We're Coming to America, Morning Has Broken, and many other's were masterfully done because he is an icon, and this was a fun treat.
